SIMPLE: flashy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flashy
<hw>Flash"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Dazzling
for a moment; making a momentary show of brilliancy; transitorily
bright.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A little <qex>flashy</qex> and transient pleasure.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fiery; vehement; impetuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A temper always <qex>flashy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Showy; gay; gaudy; <as>as, a <ex>flashy</ex>
dress</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Without taste or spirit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lean and <qex>flashy</qex> songs.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flask</ent>⟦br⟧
